Latest Composer Installation (PHP Dependency Manager)

Composer can be installed in Windows, Linux, and macOS. The recommended method is official installer + CLI setup.

🔷 1. Requirements Before Installation

Make sure you already have:

✔ PHP installed (minimum recommended)
PHP ≥ 8.0 (better: 8.2+)
Check:
php -v

✔ OpenSSL enabled
✔ Internet connection
💻 2. Installation on Windows (Latest Method)
🔷 Step 1: Download Installer

Go to official site:
👉 https://getcomposer.org/download/

Download:
👉 Composer-Setup.exe

🔷 Step 2: Run Installer
Double click .exe
It will automatically detect PHP path (XAMPP/WAMP)
If not detected, manually select:
C:\xampp\php\php.exe

🔷 Step 3: Install
Click NEXT → INSTALL
It will set PATH automatically
🔷 Step 4: Verify Installation

Open CMD:

composer -V


✔ Output example:

Composer version 2.x.x 2026-xx-xx

🐧 3. Installation on Linux (Ubuntu/Debian – Latest CLI Method)
🔷 Step 1: Update system
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

🔷 Step 2: Install dependencies
sudo apt install php-cli unzip curl -y

🔷 Step 3: Download Composer installer
curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer -o composer-setup.php

🔷 Step 4: Verify installer (important security step)
HASH=$(curl -sS https://composer.github.io/installer.sig)

php -r "if (hash_file('sha384', 'composer-setup.php') === '$HASH') { echo 'Installer verified'; } else { echo 'Corrupt installer'; unlink('composer-setup.php'); } echo PHP_EOL;"

🔷 Step 5: Install Composer globally
sudo php composer-setup.php --install-dir=/usr/local/bin --filename=composer

🔷 Step 6: Verify
composer -V

🍎 4. Installation on macOS (Latest Method)
🔷 Step 1: Use Homebrew (Recommended)
brew install composer

🔷 Step 2: Verify
composer -V

🔷 5. Alternative Global Installer Method (All OS)
php -r "copy('https://getcomposer.org/installer', 'composer-setup.php');"
php composer-setup.php
php -r "unlink('composer-setup.php');"


Move globally:

mv composer.phar /usr/local/bin/composer

🔷 6. Verify Installation (Important)
composer -V


or

composer --version

